info.description:
# Shipping API documentation

To create, order, and retrieve labels for Shipment and Trailer, we build the Shipping API.

For C# users also provide our `Contracts` via a [nuget package](https://www.nuget.org/packages/Viya.Shipping.Contracts).

parameters.name: ExcludeHandlingUnits
parameters.description:
Prevents the handling units from being included in the response. This increases performance on the list get.
            
A count of handling units on each shipment will still be included

parameters.name: ReferenceSearch
parameters.description: Search by all references on a shipment. This is not a partial text search. The text must be an exact match

parameters.name: ConsignmentId
parameters.description: Filters the shipments by the consignmentId. This will return all shipments that are part of the consignment

parameters.name: Id
parameters.description: Item Id for exact match. If set then no filter is applied based on any other properties

parameters.name: Sort
parameters.description:
Sort definition for the list request. Should contain field names to sort in order of importance.
To sort descending, prefix the field name with a minus `-` character

parameters.name: Filter
parameters.description:
Any filters. Filters should be formatted thus: PATH:VALUE
            
e.g. addresses.sender.CompanyName:IKEA B.V.
            
Multiple filters with the same key will be treated as OR conditions.
Filters with different keys will be treated as AND conditions.
            
You can add #R# prefix to the value to indicate that it should be treated as a prefix regular expression.

(optional) Type of aggregation when the `FieldPath` yields multiple results. Default: `single`.

- `single`: returns `true` if a single result is valid; will throw if no or multiple results are found
- `all`: returns `true` if all results are valid, `true` if no results are found
- `any`: returns `true` at least one result is valid, `false` if no results are found
- `none`: returns `true` if none of the results are valid, `true` if no results are found
